==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hussar
<hw>Hus*sar"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Hung.
<ets>husz⟦aacute⟧r</ets>, from <ets>husz</ets> twenty, because under
King Matthais I., in the fifteenth century, every twenty houses were to
furnish one horse soldier; cf. G. <ets>husar</ets>, F.
<ets>houssard</ets>, <ets>hussard</ets>, from the same source.]</ety>
<fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>Originally, one of the national cavalry of
Hungary and Croatia; now, one of the light cavalry of European
armies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

